               <p>CHARLES BOTT. I am <rs id="t18321129-107-viclabel601" type="occupation">waiter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18321129-107-victim1020 t18321129-107-viclabel601"></join> at the <placeName id="t18321129-107-crimeloc602">Yorkshire Stingo</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18321129-107-crimeloc602" type="placeName" value="Yorkshire Stingo"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18321129-107-crimeloc602" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18321129-107-off599 t18321129-107-crimeloc602"></join>; the billiard-room is on one side of the green. I lost these balls on the 10th of November, off the table - I do not know the prisoner - it was a private table, and I always kept the key of it - I had seen them all safe at six o'clock, there were two sets on the table, and some persons were playing in the next room, but the door of the private room was locked.</p>
